MODULES:
Collection of terraform files.
Every resource is a module.
Root module
Child module --> VPC, subnet, igw, nat

Child modules are called in the root modules.

Root module(main.tf, output.tf, variables.tf, provider.tf, terraform.tfvars)

Child module
VPC --> main.tf, output.tf, variable.tf
Subnet --> main.tf, output.tf, variable.tf

Why?
	1. Reusability --> different env, different projects.
	2. Reduce repeated code --> calling child modules.
	3. Better organisation -->breaking infra from large to small.
	4. Team collaboraton: different teams manage different modules.
	Vpc module --> networking team
	Ec2 + autoscaling grp --> devops team
	RDS module --> database team
	
	
	
	
	
